---
description: Infrastructure, deployment and release rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Builds must be reproducible.
- Pin tool, chart, image and dependency versions.
- Do not use mutable image tags.
- Keep environment configuration centralized.
- Separate secrets from non-secret configuration.
- Use Helm lint and template validation.
- Validate Kubernetes manifests.
- Add readiness, liveness and startup probes where relevant.
- Add resource requests and limits.
- Use persistent volumes for stateful services.
- Make bootstrap scripts idempotent.
- Make failures observable.
- Provide rollback or recovery instructions.
- Treat release artifacts as first-class outputs.
- Generate checksums.
- Generate SBOMs.
- Do not claim deployment success without runtime evidence.
- Do not modify ArgoCD applications outside the corresponding issue scope.
